cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper presents an approach to training neural networks for sequence generation, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces actor-critic methods from reinforcement learning (RL), which are commonly used in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed method to machine translation, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
